+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014d8hmF9z9W6bPSr3i1BHGi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting autopilot. I'll narrate each decision. Jump in anytime to override.\n\n**Q1: File structure — single file or multiple?**\n→ Choosing: **Multiple files** — `store.ts` (main class), `merge.ts` (three-way merge logic), `types.ts` (interfaces), `index.ts` (re-exports)\nReasoning: The merge logic is the most complex part and benefits from isolation. Types are shared. Keeps files focused.\n\n**Q2: Internal data model for branches?**\n→ Choosing: **Map of branch name → Map of docId → document state (versions array + deleted flag)**\nReasoning: Each branch needs independent document state. Storing versions per-document-per-branch allows efficient history retrieval. A \"snapshot\" at branch creation copies the current state.\n\n**Q3: How to track branch divergence point for three-way merge?**\n→ Choosing: **Snapshot-on-branch-create** — when creating a branch, deep-clone the source branch's current state as the \"base\" for future merges.\nReasoning: This is simpler than tracking commit DAGs. The spec says \"find the common ancestor state (the point where the branches diverged)\" — storing the snapshot at divergence is the most direct approach.\n\n**Q4: Deep diff algorithm for structural merge?**\n→ Choosing: **Recursive key-by-key comparison** — walk both objects against the base, track dot-separated paths, detect conflicts at leaf level.\nReasoning: The spec requires dot-separated paths for conflicts. Arrays are treated as atomic values (compared by deep equality). This keeps the algorithm straightforward.\n\n**Q5: ID generation for versions?**\n→ Choosing: **Simple counter-based IDs** (e.g., `v1`, `v2`, `v3`)\nReasoning: Spec just says \"unique id.\" A monotonic counter is deterministic and testable.\n\n**Q6: Deep clone strategy?**\n→ Choosing: **`structuredClone`** (available in Node 17+, project targets ES2022)\nReasoning: Native, handles nested objects/arrays, no dependencies needed.\n\nProceeding to design document."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":233,"cache_read_input_tokens":23583,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":233},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65217848-ff6a-4f28-aa9f-9d37ed08c250","uuid":"7d4eb943-26cb-44f6-8114-acb8d02ba80e"}
