+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Ko1ALZF1xqJjfgW4GrpXvb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TLWDH3KSrnryrDdwBVSwHN","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-versioned-document-store-design.md","content":"# Versioned Document Store — Design\n\n## Architecture\n\n### File Structure\n- `src/types.ts` — Interfaces (DocumentStore, Version, MergeResult, Conflict)\n- `src/merge.ts` — Three-way structural merge algorithm\n- `src/store.ts` — DocumentStore class implementation\n- `src/index.ts` — Re-exports\n\n### Internal Data Model\n\n```\nBranchState = Map<docId, DocumentState>\nDocumentState = { versions: Version[], deleted: boolean }\n```\n\nStore holds:\n- `branches: Map<string, BranchState>` — per-branch document states\n- `branchBases: Map<string, Map<string, BranchState>>` — snapshot of source branch at time of fork, keyed by `childBranch → parentBranch → state`\n- `currentBranch: string` — defaults to \"main\"\n- `versionCounter: number` — monotonic counter for version IDs\n\n### Branch Creation\nWhen `createBranch(name, fromBranch?)` is called:\n1. Deep-clone the source branch's current state\n2. Store as the new branch's state\n3. Store the source branch's current state as the base snapshot in `branchBases`\n\n### Three-Way Merge Algorithm\n`merge(sourceBranch)` into current branch:\n1. Look up base snapshot (state of current branch when source was created, OR state of source when current was created — whichever exists)\n2. For each document across base, ours (current), theirs (source):\n   - If only in one side → take that side\n   - If deleted on one side only → delete\n   - If both modified → recursive field-by-field diff against base\n3. Recursive diff walks object keys, builds dot-separated paths\n4. Leaf conflict: base≠ours AND base≠theirs AND ours≠theirs → Conflict\n5. If no conflicts: apply merge, return `applied: true`\n6. If conflicts: don't apply, return `applied: false`, merged uses \"ours\" for conflicted fields\n\n### Deep Clone\nUse `structuredClone()` for all storage/retrieval boundaries.\n\n### Version IDs\nMonotonic counter: `v1`, `v2`, `v3`, etc.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":107,"cache_read_input_tokens":24517,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":107},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65217848-ff6a-4f28-aa9f-9d37ed08c250","uuid":"f97f7ccb-1766-451b-b0fd-fa6a08d12666"}
